"use strict";(self.webpackChunkbump_sh_github_io=self.webpackChunkbump_sh_github_io||[]).push([[8536],{2805:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"blogPosts":[{"id":"/2023/06/03/lightning-fast-api-documentation-rendering","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2023/06/03/lightning-fast-api-documentation-rendering","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2023-06-03-lightning-fast-api-documentation-rendering.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2023-06-03-lightning-fast-api-documentation-rendering.md","title":"Lightning-fast API Documentation rendering","description":"improved-access-management.png","date":"2023-06-03T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"June 3, 2023","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Lightning-fast API Documentation rendering","tags":["Improvement"],"image":"/files/changelog/bump-sh-performance-enhancements.png"},"nextItem":{"title":"Enhanced Specifications Support","permalink":"/product-updates/2023/01/27/enhanced-specifications-support"}},"content":"![improved-access-management.png](/files/changelog/bump-sh-performance-enhancements.png)\\n\\nFast-loading page is a must these days, both for human users and search engines.\\n\\nThanks to the new rendering engine, which has already been released to 100% of our users, navigating your API documentation is now a breeze. It provides an optimal experience for all API consumers, whatever the size of the documentation (yes, any size).\\n\\nPerformance is significantly better: the first interactive content is as fast as the blink of an eye, which also means there\'s no more blocking time when you first navigate the API documentation."},{"id":"/2023/01/27/enhanced-specifications-support","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2023/01/27/enhanced-specifications-support","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2023-01-27-enhanced-specifications-support.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2023-01-27-enhanced-specifications-support.md","title":"Enhanced Specifications Support","description":"Over the past weeks, we have considerably enhanced our support of the specifications.","date":"2023-01-27T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"January 27, 2023","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Enhanced Specifications Support","tags":["Improvement"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Lightning-fast API Documentation rendering","permalink":"/product-updates/2023/06/03/lightning-fast-api-documentation-rendering"},"nextItem":{"title":"Improved Access Management","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/12/07/improved-access-management"}},"content":"Over the past weeks, we have considerably enhanced our support of the specifications.\\n\\n## minLength, maxLength and pattern\\n\\nWherever you need to document restrictions on string fields, OpenAPI and AsyncAPI specifications rely on JSON Schema to support this.\\n`minLength` and `maxLength`  are meant to constrain the length of a string.\\n`pattern`  restrict the string to a specific Regular Expression (regex).\\n\\nEmail addresses, IBANs and ZIP/Postal codes could be great examples of these features.\\n\\n\\n![minlength-example.png](/files/changelog/minlength-example.png)\\n\\n\\n## readOnly  and  writeOnly  properties\\n\\nJSON Schema allows defining a property as `readOnly`  or  `writeOnly`.\\nMany examples can easily be imagined when used with AsyncAPI or OpenAPI : `readOnly`  timestamp, `writeOnly`  password, etc...\\n\\nOur [Help Center](https://docs.bump.sh/help/specifications-support/asyncapi-support/#readonly-and-writeonly-properties) shares more details on how Bump.sh works with this feature and a few examples."},{"id":"/2022/12/07/improved-access-management","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2022/12/07/improved-access-management","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2022-12-07-improved-access-management.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2022-12-07-improved-access-management.md","title":"Improved Access Management","description":"improved-access-management.png","date":"2022-12-07T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"December 7, 2022","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Improved Access Management","tags":["Improvement"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Enhanced Specifications Support","permalink":"/product-updates/2023/01/27/enhanced-specifications-support"},"nextItem":{"title":"Polymorphism","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/11/14/polymorphism"}},"content":"![improved-access-management.png](/files/changelog/improved-access-management.png)\\n\\nAccess management has been reshaped, thanks to extended tests and user feedback.\\n\\nInviting external customers and partners to access internal APIs is now possible directly from the dashboard.\\n\\nFrom the dedicated section in your hub/documentation settings, you can quickly modify who has access to what. Open it to teammates of your organization, or invite external partners by email directly.\\n\\nPassword-protected level will stay available for a limited amount of time. More info can be found in our [help center](https://docs.bump.sh/help/access-management/)."},{"id":"/2022/11/14/polymorphism","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2022/11/14/polymorphism","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2022-11-14-polymorphism.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2022-11-14-polymorphism.md","title":"Polymorphism","description":"They have many names: schema alternatives, discriminator, inheritance... but you probably know them as oneOf, anyOf and allOf.","date":"2022-11-14T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"November 14, 2022","tags":[{"label":"New","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/new"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Polymorphism","tags":["New"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Improved Access Management","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/12/07/improved-access-management"},"nextItem":{"title":"Automated Image Generation","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/09/05/automated-image-generation"}},"content":"They have many names: schema alternatives, discriminator, inheritance... but you probably know them as oneOf, anyOf and allOf.\\n\\nBump now fully supports polymorphism for AsyncAPI and OpenAPI. You can already upload your latest API specification file to check it out. Or see it in action with our [demo documentation of the feature](https://bump.sh/bump/doc/petstore-alternatives#operation-post-pets-body-animal-cat-species-species-alternative)!\\n\\n![polymorphism.png](/files/changelog/polymorphism.png)"},{"id":"/2022/09/05/automated-image-generation","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2022/09/05/automated-image-generation","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2022-09-05-automated-image-generation.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2022-09-05-automated-image-generation.md","title":"Automated Image Generation","description":"After working so hard on your API and its documentation, the moment has come to share it with the world.","date":"2022-09-05T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"September 5, 2022","tags":[{"label":"New","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/new"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Automated Image Generation","tags":["New"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Polymorphism","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/11/14/polymorphism"},"nextItem":{"title":"Branching","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/07/08/branching"}},"content":"After working so hard on your API and its documentation, the moment has come to share it with the world.\\nWe recently released a new social network feature, that helps you create beautiful visuals pointing to your API.\\n\\nYou can now upload your own image or leave the work to us to generate a nice one. Sharing your documentation link on social networks will now display your own visual, making it more appealing.\\n\\nFind out more in our [Help Center](https://docs.bump.sh/help/meta-images/)!\\n\\n![metaimage-forto.png](/files/changelog/metaimage-forto.png)"},{"id":"/2022/07/08/branching","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2022/07/08/branching","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2022-07-08-branching.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2022-07-08-branching.md","title":"Branching","description":"Introducing Branching, a great way to host several versions of an API Specification on the same documentation.","date":"2022-07-08T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"July 8, 2022","tags":[{"label":"New","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/new"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Branching","tags":["New"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Automated Image Generation","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/09/05/automated-image-generation"},"nextItem":{"title":"Search!","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/06/13/search"}},"content":"Introducing **Branching**, a great way to host several versions of an API Specification on the same documentation.\\n\\nIf your API has several versions you would like to maintain or if you are working between two environments, branching will make a difference and limit the number of documentation in your hub.\\n\\nCreate as many branches as you need, upload files accordingly and find the versions of your API anytime in your documentation, through a small selection menu.\\n\\nDefine which branch should be chosen by default, add or delete branches, keep everything up-to-date and share with your ecosystem the best API experience possible.\\n\\n![branching.gif](/files/changelog/branching.gif)"},{"id":"/2022/06/13/search","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2022/06/13/search","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2022-06-13-search.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2022-06-13-search.md","title":"Search!","description":"Here comes a long-expected new feature the Search Bar solves this in a blink of an eye.","date":"2022-06-13T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"June 13, 2022","tags":[{"label":"New","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/new"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Search!","tags":["New"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Branching","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/07/08/branching"},"nextItem":{"title":"Multiple types for properties","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/06/04/multiple-types-for-properties copie"}},"content":"Here comes a long-expected new feature: the Search Bar. We know how time-consuming it can be to scroll through long API documentation to find what you are looking for: the Search Bar solves this in a blink of an eye.\\n\\nOur Search engine can look in your documentations and even your hubs on your APIs structures: endpoints, objects, properties, webhooks, etc... And to make it more comfortable, we sort them by types (and it looks great, seriously).\\n\\nWe are already working on two limitations: you cannot search in your spec history and we are lacking advanced filters.\\n\\nDiscoverability is an important topic on our end. We want to help teams and communities deep dive into their API ecosystem, making them easier to find and use. We will have a lot more to announce soon and we are preparing a small blog post on this feature\u2019s making-of.\\n\\nWe hope you\u2019ll enjoy the Search Bar: feel free to reach out if you have any feedback or suggestion!\\n\\n_P.S. Search will be activated on your documentation/hub after the next deploy but please contact us if you need it before this as we can manually activate it._\\n\\n![search.gif](/files/changelog/search.gif)"},{"id":"/2022/06/04/multiple-types-for-properties copie","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2022/06/04/multiple-types-for-properties copie","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2022-06-04-multiple-types-for-properties copie.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2022-06-04-multiple-types-for-properties copie.md","title":"Multiple types for properties","description":"Here is an update that was released some time ago but out of the radar: we now display all available types (even nullable) on any properties in your OpenAPI or AsyncAPI definition.","date":"2022-06-04T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"June 4, 2022","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Multiple types for properties","tags":["Improvement"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Search!","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/06/13/search"},"nextItem":{"title":"COLORS","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/05/07/colors"}},"content":"Here is an update that was released some time ago but out of the radar: we now display all available types (even `nullable`) on any properties in your OpenAPI or AsyncAPI definition. \\n\\nYou\u2019ll now see these correctly displayed properties in your documentation. Multiple types may look like a slight improvement but will add clarification to your team and community.\\n\\nAnd we have an example to show how great it is (thanks to [Meilisearch\'s documentation](https://bump.sh/doc/meilisearch#operation-indexes-documents-search-body-filter)).\\n\\n![multiple-types.png](/files/changelog/multiple-types.png)"},{"id":"/2022/05/07/colors","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2022/05/07/colors","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2022-05-07-colors.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2022-05-07-colors.md","title":"COLORS","description":"You already have deployed your API documentation but feel something\'s missing? You couldn\'t be more right.","date":"2022-05-07T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"May 7, 2022","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"COLORS","tags":["Improvement"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Multiple types for properties","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/06/04/multiple-types-for-properties copie"},"nextItem":{"title":"Webhooks","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/04/02/webhooks"}},"content":"You already have deployed your API documentation but feel something\'s missing? You couldn\'t be more right.\\n\\nIntroducing one of the biggest updates to Bump yet: **UI Color customization**. You read that right. You can now change the primary color of your documentation to make it shine more than ever. Or make it match your logo/company brand!\\n\\nWe even added a short preview to help you find the best tone and ensure that you\'ll keep in mind how it will look in dark mode too.\\n\\nTry it out from your _Dashboard > Customize UI_ and share with us your best results!\\n\\n![colors.png](/files/changelog/colors.png)"},{"id":"/2022/04/02/webhooks","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2022/04/02/webhooks","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2022-04-02-webhooks.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2022-04-02-webhooks.md","title":"Webhooks","description":"Today, we\u2019re introducing Webhooks integration, as a new way to add Bump to your existing workflow.","date":"2022-04-02T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"April 2, 2022","tags":[{"label":"New","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/new"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Webhooks","tags":["New"]},"prevItem":{"title":"COLORS","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/05/07/colors"},"nextItem":{"title":"Documentation Access","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/03/20/documentation-access"}},"content":"Today, we\u2019re introducing Webhooks integration, as a new way to add Bump to your existing workflow.\\n\\nSet them up from your dashboard and receive notifications when events on your API structure are detected on your documentation.\\n\\nFind more in our [Help Center](https://docs.bump.sh/help/api-change-management/webhooks/)!\\n\\n![webhooks_main.png](/files/changelog/webhooks_main.png)"},{"id":"/2022/03/20/documentation-access","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2022/03/20/documentation-access","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2022-03-20-documentation-access.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2022-03-20-documentation-access.md","title":"Documentation Access","description":"Following our recently released Organization feature, the new Documentation Access Management will help control who has access to which documentation or hubs.","date":"2022-03-20T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"March 20, 2022","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Documentation Access","tags":["Improvement"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Webhooks","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/04/02/webhooks"},"nextItem":{"title":"Organization support","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/03/10/organization-support"}},"content":"Following our recently released Organization feature, the new Documentation Access Management will help control who has access to which documentation or hubs.\\n\\nThree access levels are available: public, private (for your organization only) and protected (limited, password protection).\\n\\nFind more in our [Help Center](https://docs.bump.sh/help/access-management/)!\\n\\n![access-management.png](/files/changelog/access-management.png)"},{"id":"/2022/03/10/organization-support","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2022/03/10/organization-support","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2022-03-10-organization-support.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2022-03-10-organization-support.md","title":"Organization support","description":"Building the best APIs can be a considerable amount of work and you may need your teammates to help. But you definitely do not want one single shared account for that.","date":"2022-03-10T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"March 10, 2022","tags":[{"label":"New","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/new"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Organization support","tags":["New"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Documentation Access","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/03/20/documentation-access"},"nextItem":{"title":"Changelog update","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/01/15/changelog-update"}},"content":"Building the best APIs can be a considerable amount of work and you may need your teammates to help. But you definitely do not want one single shared account for that.\\n\\nFreshly out of beta, the awaited **Organizations** feature helps you with that. We did not reinvent the wheel but wanted to make it as simple but powerful as possible.\\n\\n![organization-support.png](/files/changelog/organization-support.png)\\n\\nYou can easily customize access with 3 different roles: admin, maintainer, and viewers.\\nAdmins can invite and manage access, maintainers can manage hubs and docs, guests are limited to read-only.\\n\\nAvailable from the Startup plan, we hope it will help teams work efficiently and smoothly on their APIs. You can find out more about Organizations in our [Help Center](https://docs.bump.sh/help/organizations/)!\\n\\nThis update was also the opportunity to ship some enhancements for the dashboard.\\n\\nWe can\u2019t wait to hear about what you think of it so feel free to reach out!"},{"id":"/2022/01/15/changelog-update","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2022/01/15/changelog-update","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2022-01-15-changelog-update.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2022-01-15-changelog-update.md","title":"Changelog update","description":"The API changelog page has been redesigned to give you a clearer view of what has changed inside your API, it is the groundwork of having fine-grained changelog details \ud83d\udd75\ufe0f","date":"2022-01-15T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"January 15, 2022","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Changelog update","tags":["Improvement"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Organization support","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/03/10/organization-support"},"nextItem":{"title":"Bump diff navigation","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/11/14/bump-diff-navigation"}},"content":"The API changelog page has been redesigned to give you a clearer view of what has changed inside your API, it is the groundwork of having fine-grained changelog details \ud83d\udd75\ufe0f\\n\\nHope you will enjoy it! \\n\\nSee it in action on our own API documentation: https://lnkd.in/gij9uHUy\\n\\n\u2022 Bonus point:\\n\\nIf you use our github-action, the diff comments have also been updated. Check our latest release for details: [https://github.com/bump-sh/github-action/releases/tag/v1.1.0](https://github.com/bump-sh/github-action/releases/tag/v1.1.0)\\n\\n\\n![changelog.gif](/files/changelog/changelog.gif)"},{"id":"/2021/11/14/bump-diff-navigation","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2021/11/14/bump-diff-navigation","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2021-11-14-bump-diff-navigation.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2021-11-14-bump-diff-navigation.md","title":"Bump diff navigation","description":"\u2728  Quickly identify what has changed in your API \u2728","date":"2021-11-14T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"November 14, 2021","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Bump diff navigation","tags":["Improvement"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Changelog update","permalink":"/product-updates/2022/01/15/changelog-update"},"nextItem":{"title":"Multiple examples support","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/11/08/multiple-examples-support"}},"content":"\u2728  Quickly identify what has changed in your API \u2728 \\n\\nJump from change to change! No need to scroll anymore to see the latest changes in your documentation diff.\\n\\n![diff-navigation.gif](/files/changelog/diff-navigation.gif)\\n\\nSee it in action: [https://docs.canopyservicing.com/changes/fbcf9592-a369-4f17-9adb-410d48e3ff98](https://docs.canopyservicing.com/changes/fbcf9592-a369-4f17-9adb-410d48e3ff98)"},{"id":"/2021/11/08/multiple-examples-support","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2021/11/08/multiple-examples-support","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2021-11-08-multiple-examples-support.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2021-11-08-multiple-examples-support.md","title":"Multiple examples support","description":"Give your API users a personalized experience and a better understanding of your API while reading your documentation by including multiple examples to your API definition.","date":"2021-11-08T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"November 8, 2021","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Multiple examples support","tags":["Improvement"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Bump diff navigation","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/11/14/bump-diff-navigation"},"nextItem":{"title":"Bump live preview","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/10/12/bump-live-preview"}},"content":"Give your API users a personalized experience and a better understanding of your API while reading your documentation by including multiple examples to your API definition.\\n\\nBump now supports displaying multiple examples which are supported by both OpenAPI and AsyncAPI specifications.\\n\\n![multiple_examples.jpg](/files/changelog/multiple_examples.jpg)"},{"id":"/2021/10/12/bump-live-preview","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2021/10/12/bump-live-preview","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2021-10-12-bump-live-preview.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2021-10-12-bump-live-preview.md","title":"Bump live preview","description":"A new --live flag was added to the bump preview command.","date":"2021-10-12T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"October 12, 2021","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Bump live preview","tags":["Improvement"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Multiple examples support","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/11/08/multiple-examples-support"},"nextItem":{"title":"Automatic breaking change detection","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/10/03/automatic-breaking-change-detection"}},"content":"A new `--live` flag was added to the bump `preview` command.\\n\\nThis gives you the ability to stay focused on your API definition file (OpenAPI or AsyncAPI file) while seeing your Bump preview documentation page being updated as you change the file.\\n\\nNo need for a specific text editor, or any extension, just use the bump CLI to preview your documentation live.\\n\\n![live-preview.gif](/files/changelog/live-preview.gif)\\n\\nLearn more about live preview on [our help page](https://docs.bump.sh/help/bump-cli/#live-preview)."},{"id":"/2021/10/03/automatic-breaking-change-detection","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2021/10/03/automatic-breaking-change-detection","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2021-10-03-automatic-breaking-change-detection.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2021-10-03-automatic-breaking-change-detection.md","title":"Automatic breaking change detection","description":"If some changes are more important than others, it is especially true for your API.","date":"2021-10-03T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"October 3, 2021","tags":[{"label":"New","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/new"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Automatic breaking change detection","tags":["New"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Bump live preview","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/10/12/bump-live-preview"},"nextItem":{"title":"Changelog makeover \ud83d\udc84","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/09/21/changelog-makeover"}},"content":"If some changes are more important than others, it is especially true for your API.\\n\\nFrom now on, we automatically detect if a new version of your API includes some breaking changes. It will be visible in the\xa0[changelog page](https://developers.bump.sh/changes), in the\xa0changelog email or the brand new RSS feed\u2026 but also during your API design phase while opening a pull request thanks to\xa0[our Github Action](https://github.com/bump-sh/github-action/).\\n\\n\\n![breaking_changes.png](/files/changelog/breaking_changes.png)\\n\\n\\nWith Bump, you will never miss a _breaking_ change again."},{"id":"/2021/09/21/changelog-makeover","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2021/09/21/changelog-makeover","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2021-09-21-changelog-makeover.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2021-09-21-changelog-makeover.md","title":"Changelog makeover \ud83d\udc84","description":"changelogrevamp.jpg","date":"2021-09-21T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"September 21, 2021","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Changelog makeover \ud83d\udc84","tags":["Improvement"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Automatic breaking change detection","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/10/03/automatic-breaking-change-detection"},"nextItem":{"title":"RSS feed for your changelog","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/09/20/rss-feed-for-your-changelog"}},"content":"![changelog_revamp.jpg](/files/changelog/changelog_revamp.jpg)\\n\\n\\nWe redesigned the whole changelog page in order to bring you a better understanding of changes history of your API.\\n\\nHere\'s an example: https://developers.bump.sh/changes"},{"id":"/2021/09/20/rss-feed-for-your-changelog","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2021/09/20/rss-feed-for-your-changelog","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2021-09-20-rss-feed-for-your-changelog.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2021-09-20-rss-feed-for-your-changelog.md","title":"RSS feed for your changelog","description":"back.jpg","date":"2021-09-20T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"September 20, 2021","tags":[{"label":"New","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/new"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"RSS feed for your changelog","tags":["New"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Changelog makeover \ud83d\udc84","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/09/21/changelog-makeover"},"nextItem":{"title":"Bindings support for AsyncAPI","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/09/16/bindings-support-for-asyncapi"}},"content":"![back.jpg](/files/changelog/back.jpg)\\n\\nIn the age of information overload, getting access to information that matters can be quite challenging and that\'s exactly the purpose of RSS.\\n\\nFrom now, get notified of the API changes through RSS in addition to the existing email.\\n\\nGive it a try with the [Bump RSS feed](https://developers.bump.sh/changes.rss) in your favorite RSS reader."},{"id":"/2021/09/16/bindings-support-for-asyncapi","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2021/09/16/bindings-support-for-asyncapi","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2021-09-16-bindings-support-for-asyncapi.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2021-09-16-bindings-support-for-asyncapi.md","title":"Bindings support for AsyncAPI","description":"bindingsasyncapibump.png","date":"2021-09-16T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"September 16, 2021","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Bindings support for AsyncAPI","tags":["Improvement"]},"prevItem":{"title":"RSS feed for your changelog","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/09/20/rss-feed-for-your-changelog"},"nextItem":{"title":"Share and highlight anything inside your API documentation","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/09/11/share-and-highlight-anything-inside-your-api-documentation"}},"content":"![bindings_asyncapi_bump.png](/files/changelog/bindings_asyncapi_bump.png)\\n\\nAsyncAPI users, you\'ll be happy to know that Bump now supports bindings.\\n\\nAs AsyncAPI allows many protocols, which is really nice, bindings are a useful and necessary mechanism to define protocol-specific information. Bump now displays protocol information defined at server, operation, and message levels, as part of an ongoing work for a better understanding of API documentations.\\n\\nHere\'s an example: [https://bump.sh/hub/examples/doc/asyncapi-user-signup#protocol-information](https://bump.sh/hub/examples/doc/asyncapi-user-signup#protocol-information)"},{"id":"/2021/09/11/share-and-highlight-anything-inside-your-api-documentation","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2021/09/11/share-and-highlight-anything-inside-your-api-documentation","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2021-09-11-share-and-highlight-anything-inside-your-api-documentation.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2021-09-11-share-and-highlight-anything-inside-your-api-documentation.md","title":"Share and highlight anything inside your API documentation","description":"To give your users the best API onboarding,","date":"2021-09-11T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"September 11, 2021","tags":[{"label":"New","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/new"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Share and highlight anything inside your API documentation","tags":["New"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Bindings support for AsyncAPI","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/09/16/bindings-support-for-asyncapi"},"nextItem":{"title":"Markdown support","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/09/07/markdown-support"}},"content":"To give your users the best API onboarding, \\nit often helps to be able to share specific pieces of information. \\n\\nThanks to this new feature, you can now share and highlight anything in your API documentation with just a click. The selected element will be highlighted following your color theme.\\n\\n![share_highlight.gif](/files/changelog/share_highlight.gif)\\n\\nGive it a try: [https://developers.bump.sh/#post-previews-body](https://developers.bump.sh/#post-previews-body)"},{"id":"/2021/09/07/markdown-support","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2021/09/07/markdown-support","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2021-09-07-markdown-support.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2021-09-07-markdown-support.md","title":"Markdown support","description":"markdown-callouts.jpg","date":"2021-09-07T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"September 7, 2021","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Markdown support","tags":["Improvement"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Share and highlight anything inside your API documentation","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/09/11/share-and-highlight-anything-inside-your-api-documentation"},"nextItem":{"title":"Receive API changelog in your mailbox \ud83d\udd14","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/07/18/receive-api-changelog-in-your-mailbox"}},"content":"![markdown-callouts.jpg](/files/changelog/markdown-callouts.jpg)\\n\\nAs markdown is a standard and a common way to bring more readability into your documentation, we have made some improvements on markdown support and bring new features to help you create fast and beautiful API documentations.\\n\\nBump now supports common Markdown syntax, language color syntax highlighting, and information call-outs. Last but not least, Markdown can be included inside your contract file or as an external reference using dedicated Markdown files.\\n\\nCheck [our help page](https://docs.bump.sh/help/specifications-support/markdown-support/) to start taking advantage of markdown in your API documentation."},{"id":"/2021/07/18/receive-api-changelog-in-your-mailbox","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2021/07/18/receive-api-changelog-in-your-mailbox","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2021-07-18-receive-api-changelog-in-your-mailbox.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2021-07-18-receive-api-changelog-in-your-mailbox.md","title":"Receive API changelog in your mailbox \ud83d\udd14","description":"email-notif.png","date":"2021-07-18T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"July 18, 2021","tags":[{"label":"New","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/new"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Receive API changelog in your mailbox \ud83d\udd14","tags":["New"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Markdown support","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/09/07/markdown-support"},"nextItem":{"title":"Download source from your documentation","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/07/13/download-source-from-your-documentation"}},"content":"![email-notif.png](/files/changelog/email-notif.png)\\n\\nIn API documentation, changelogs are important, and your API consumers need to stay up-to-date on recent changes.\\n\\nIt\'s now possible for them to subscribe by email to your API changelog: they will receive a summary of the changelog every week in their mailbox!\\n\\nWant to see it in action on Bump API documentation? [See it live](https://developers.bump.sh/changes)\\n\\nDo not hesitate to invite your API consumers to subscribe to your API updates (available at `http://{your-doc-url}/changes`)\\n\\n_Never miss an API change again_ (now, it\'s in your mailbox in case you missed it \ud83d\ude09)"},{"id":"/2021/07/13/download-source-from-your-documentation","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2021/07/13/download-source-from-your-documentation","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2021-07-13-download-source-from-your-documentation.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2021-07-13-download-source-from-your-documentation.md","title":"Download source from your documentation","description":"download-source.png","date":"2021-07-13T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"July 13, 2021","tags":[{"label":"New","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/new"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Download source from your documentation","tags":["New"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Receive API changelog in your mailbox \ud83d\udd14","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/07/18/receive-api-changelog-in-your-mailbox"},"nextItem":{"title":"Bump diff from your Command Line Interface or your Continuous Integration platform","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/07/02/bump-diff-from-your-cli"}},"content":"![download-source.png](/files/changelog/download-source.png)\\n\\nWe\'ve made it easy for API consumers to [download the source](https://developers.bump.sh/) of an API documentation.\\n\\nWhether you want to get your hands on a `JSON` or `YAML` format, for `OpenAPI` or `AsyncAPI`, you\'re now just a click away."},{"id":"/2021/07/02/bump-diff-from-your-cli","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2021/07/02/bump-diff-from-your-cli","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2021-07-02-bump-diff-from-your-cli.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2021-07-02-bump-diff-from-your-cli.md","title":"Bump diff from your Command Line Interface or your Continuous Integration platform","description":"Our new bump diff command has landed in our CLI.","date":"2021-07-02T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"July 2, 2021","tags":[{"label":"New","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/new"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Bump diff from your Command Line Interface or your Continuous Integration platform","tags":["New"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Download source from your documentation","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/07/13/download-source-from-your-documentation"},"nextItem":{"title":"Nested properties get a make up \ud83c\udf80","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/06/09/nested-properties-get-a-make-up"}},"content":"Our [new bump `diff` command](https://www.npmjs.com/package/bump-cli#bump-diff-file) has landed in our CLI. <br/>\\n_Make sure to [upgrade your `bump-cli` package](https://github.com/bump-sh/cli/releases/tag/v2.1.0) to at least `v2.1.0` to test it._\\n\\nNow, straight from your CLI, you are able to describe the changes made in your contract:\\n\\n```sh\\n> bump diff --doc users-account api-specification.yaml\\nUpdated: GET /account\\n  Response modified: 200\\n    Body attribute added: ticket_ids\\nAdded: GET /tickets/{ticket_id}\\n```\\n\\nThe new command will output a quick summary of what has changed between your latest deployed API contract and the file you have changed locally.\\n\\nIf you use Github Actions to launch your automation workflows, we have some more good news for you: [we now offer a stable `bump-sh/github-action@v1` action](https://github.com/bump-sh/github-action/releases/tag/v1.0.0). And this latest release includes **automatic API contract changelog pushed as a comment for each pull request**.\\n\\nCheck [our help page](https://docs.bump.sh/help/continuous-integration/github-actions/#api-diff-on-pull-requests--deploy-on-push) to get you started with team collaboration on API design."},{"id":"/2021/06/09/nested-properties-get-a-make-up","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2021/06/09/nested-properties-get-a-make-up","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2021-06-09-nested-properties-get-a-make-up.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2021-06-09-nested-properties-get-a-make-up.md","title":"Nested properties get a make up \ud83c\udf80","description":"nested-properties.jpg","date":"2021-06-09T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"June 9, 2021","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Nested properties get a make up \ud83c\udf80","tags":["Improvement"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Bump diff from your Command Line Interface or your Continuous Integration platform","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/07/02/bump-diff-from-your-cli"},"nextItem":{"title":"New Command Line Interface era","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/05/29/new-command-line-interface-era"}},"content":"![nested-properties.jpg](/files/changelog/nested-properties.jpg)\\n\\nFeedbacks are important to us and we do our best to make you feel heard.\\nWe know that accessing nested properties is a pain point for many of you so we tried to make the navigation clearer and the selected element will now stand out more.\\n\\nWe\'d love to hear from you and see if these changes suit your needs so hit us up with [your comments](mailto:hello@bump.sh) whether you love it or hate it!"},{"id":"/2021/05/29/new-command-line-interface-era","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2021/05/29/new-command-line-interface-era","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2021-05-29-new-command-line-interface-era.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2021-05-29-new-command-line-interface-era.md","title":"New Command Line Interface era","description":"new-cli.gif","date":"2021-05-29T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"May 29, 2021","tags":[{"label":"New","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/new"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"New Command Line Interface era","tags":["New"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Nested properties get a make up \ud83c\udf80","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/06/09/nested-properties-get-a-make-up"},"nextItem":{"title":"Ease your sight with dark mode \u263e","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/05/23/ease-your-sight-with-dark-mode"}},"content":"![new-cli.gif](/files/changelog/new-cli.gif)\\n\\nGoodbye to our legacy ruby gem, and hello to our new node-based CLI \ud83d\udc4b.\\n\\nWe are releasing a new Command Line Interface which is iso-feature with the old CLI. There is one additional improvement though: **we now support recursive external references** (`$ref` keyword in your API specifications), with mixed filesystem or URL paths. You can now refactor your API definitions in small chunks, re-use parts of it, and separate concerns between endpoints, models or nested-objects in peace.\\n\\n\\nThis new CLI package is written in Typescript which will help us to publish a stable & type safe tool. On top of that -and especially with the [oclif](https://oclif.io/) framework- we are now able to publish universal packages for multiple OSes & architectures so everybody can enjoy Bump via command line interface.\\n\\n## Get it while it\'s hot \\n\\n```\\nnpm install -g bump-cli\\n```\\n\\nor download a package directly from the [latest Github release](https://github.com/bump-sh/cli/releases) assets.\\n\\n## Enjoy the commands\\n\\n- [`bump preview`](https://github.com/bump-sh/bump-node-cli#bump-preview-file) to build as many API documentation preview as you want. \\n- [`bump deploy --dry-run`](https://github.com/bump-sh/bump-node-cli#bump-deploy-file) to validate your future API documentation deployment.\\n  \\n  _(\u26a0\ufe0f This is a breaking change compared to our old CLI\'s and replaces the old `bump validate` command)_\\n- [`bump deploy`](https://github.com/bump-sh/bump-node-cli#bump-deploy-file) to deploy your latest API documentation changes."},{"id":"/2021/05/23/ease-your-sight-with-dark-mode","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2021/05/23/ease-your-sight-with-dark-mode","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2021-05-23-ease-your-sight-with-dark-mode.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2021-05-23-ease-your-sight-with-dark-mode.md","title":"Ease your sight with dark mode \u263e","description":"darkmode.jpg","date":"2021-05-23T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"May 23, 2021","tags":[{"label":"New","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/new"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Ease your sight with dark mode \u263e","tags":["New"]},"prevItem":{"title":"New Command Line Interface era","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/05/29/new-command-line-interface-era"},"nextItem":{"title":"Documentations in your pocket","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/05/20/documentation-in-your-pocket"}},"content":"![darkmode.jpg](/files/changelog/darkmode.jpg)\\n\\nToday we introduce the dark mode to your documentations! Depending on your system settings, your page will appear in a light mode (default) or in a darker scheme.\\n\\nYou\'ll also be able to toggle to light or dark mode regarding your own preferences.\\n\\nWe hope you will enjoy the new experience. \ud83d\udc7b"},{"id":"/2021/05/20/documentation-in-your-pocket","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2021/05/20/documentation-in-your-pocket","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2021-05-20-documentation-in-your-pocket.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2021-05-20-documentation-in-your-pocket.md","title":"Documentations in your pocket","description":"mobile-version.jpg","date":"2021-05-20T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"May 20, 2021","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Documentations in your pocket","tags":["Improvement"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Ease your sight with dark mode \u263e","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/05/23/ease-your-sight-with-dark-mode"},"nextItem":{"title":"Global support of external references","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/03/16/global-support-of-external-references"}},"content":"![mobile-version.jpg](/files/changelog/mobile-version.jpg)\\n\\nWe now offer a better mobile experience for your documentation if you happen to need it on-the-go. You will also have a navigation menu that allows to access the changelog page.\\n \\nMore changes are coming, stay tuned!"},{"id":"/2021/03/16/global-support-of-external-references","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2021/03/16/global-support-of-external-references","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2021-03-16-global-support-of-external-references.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2021-03-16-global-support-of-external-references.md","title":"Global support of external references","description":"As your API grows, your specification becomes more and more complex. At some point, splitting it up into multiple files with $ref references pointing to these external resources can help a lot.","date":"2021-03-16T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"March 16, 2021","tags":[{"label":"New","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/new"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Global support of external references","tags":["New"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Documentations in your pocket","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/05/20/documentation-in-your-pocket"},"nextItem":{"title":"Hello, OpenAPI webhooks","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/02/04/hello-openapi-webhooks"}},"content":"As your API grows, your specification becomes more and more complex. At some point, splitting it up into multiple files with `$ref` references pointing to these external resources can help a lot.\\n\\nWe have just released full external references support  by updating:\\n* our web app\\n* our CLI ([version 0.7 is out](https://github.com/bump-sh/bump-cli/releases/tag/v0.7.0))\\n* our GitHub action ([version 0.2 is out](https://github.com/marketplace/actions/api-documentation-on-bump))\\n\\nNow, no matter the channel you use to deploy a specification, Bump will resolve all references (when possible) and import their content into your documentation.\\n\\nWant to learn more? Have a look at [our documentation](https://docs.bump.sh/help/specifications-support/references/)."},{"id":"/2021/02/04/hello-openapi-webhooks","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2021/02/04/hello-openapi-webhooks","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2021-02-04-hello-openapi-webhooks.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2021-02-04-hello-openapi-webhooks.md","title":"Hello, OpenAPI webhooks","description":"openapi-webhooks.png","date":"2021-02-04T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"February 4, 2021","tags":[{"label":"New","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/new"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Hello, OpenAPI webhooks","tags":["New"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Global support of external references","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/03/16/global-support-of-external-references"},"nextItem":{"title":"Customize operation URL","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/01/10/customize-operation-url"}},"content":"![openapi-webhooks.png](/files/changelog/openapi-webhooks.png)\\n\\n[OpenAPI 3.1](https://github.com/OAI/OpenAPI-Specification/blob/master/versions/3.1.0.md) has been released today. Some important changes are coming with this new version. Above all, the greatest improvement is the support of `webhooks`, at the same first level than `paths`.\\n\\nWe are glad to announce today that webhooks are now supported by Bump, as you can see in this [live example](https://bump.sh/doc/webhook-example).\\n\\nWe hope you\'ll enjoy this new feature, don\'t hesitate to have a look to our [technical documentation](https://docs.bump.sh/help/specifications-support/openapi-support/webhooks/) if necessary."},{"id":"/2021/01/10/customize-operation-url","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2021/01/10/customize-operation-url","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2021-01-10-customize-operation-url.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2021-01-10-customize-operation-url.md","title":"Customize operation URL","description":"OpenAPI provides field servers on OperationObject, as an alternative url to service an operation.","date":"2021-01-10T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"January 10, 2021","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Customize operation URL","tags":["Improvement"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Hello, OpenAPI webhooks","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/02/04/hello-openapi-webhooks"},"nextItem":{"title":"Custom domain for everyone","permalink":"/product-updates/2020/12/01/custom-domain-for-everyone"}},"content":"OpenAPI provides field `servers` on OperationObject, as an alternative url to service an operation.\\n> If an alternative server object is specified at the Path Item Object or Root level, it will be overridden by this value. cf [OpenAPI-Specification](https://github.com/OAI/OpenAPI-Specification/blob/master/versions/3.0.0.md#operationObject)\\n\\nFrom now on, Operations `servers` are supported to customize your operations examples (in definition and curl example)."},{"id":"/2020/12/01/custom-domain-for-everyone","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2020/12/01/custom-domain-for-everyone","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2020-12-01-custom-domain-for-everyone.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2020-12-01-custom-domain-for-everyone.md","title":"Custom domain for everyone","description":"custom-domains.png","date":"2020-12-01T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"December 1, 2020","tags":[{"label":"New","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/new"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Custom domain for everyone","tags":["New"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Customize operation URL","permalink":"/product-updates/2021/01/10/customize-operation-url"},"nextItem":{"title":"Depreciation Support","permalink":"/product-updates/2020/11/22/depreciation-support"}},"content":"![custom-domains.png](/files/changelog/custom-domains.png)\\n\\nYou can now [configure your custom domain](https://docs.bump.sh/help/custom-domains) directly from the app. No more manual email to us, just create your CNAME record, fill the form, and voil\xe0.\\n\\nWe also have good news for you: we\'ve updated our pricing plans to allow you to set up custom domains on free plans. One would say it\'s Christmas, before Christmas. Enjoy!"},{"id":"/2020/11/22/depreciation-support","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2020/11/22/depreciation-support","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2020-11-22-depreciation-support.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2020-11-22-depreciation-support.md","title":"Depreciation Support","description":"depreciation-support.png","date":"2020-11-22T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"November 22, 2020","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Depreciation Support","tags":["Improvement"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Custom domain for everyone","permalink":"/product-updates/2020/12/01/custom-domain-for-everyone"},"nextItem":{"title":"Show verbs in navigation","permalink":"/product-updates/2020/11/18/show-verbs-in-navigation"}},"content":"![depreciation-support.png](/files/changelog/depreciation-support.png)\\n\\nWe now identify deprecated elements in both OpenApi and AsyncApi specifications, and highlight them in your documentations.\\n\\nWe wanted to release it fast, as it was an important missing feature, but this is just the beginning: we have a lot of ideas on how we can enhance deprecation support that we will implement in the upcoming weeks.\\n\\nWant to share some use cases with us? [Pick a slot on Anthony\'s calendar](https://calendly.com/bump-anthony/30-min-meeting), he will be super glad to hear from you."},{"id":"/2020/11/18/show-verbs-in-navigation","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2020/11/18/show-verbs-in-navigation","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2020-11-18-show-verbs-in-navigation.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2020-11-18-show-verbs-in-navigation.md","title":"Show verbs in navigation","description":"verbs-in-navigation-zoom.png","date":"2020-11-18T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"November 18, 2020","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Show verbs in navigation","tags":["Improvement"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Depreciation Support","permalink":"/product-updates/2020/11/22/depreciation-support"},"nextItem":{"title":"Add a favicon to your documentation","permalink":"/product-updates/2020/11/12/add-a-favicon-to-your-documentation"}},"content":"![verbs-in-navigation-zoom.png](/files/changelog/verbs-in-nav.png)\\n\\nDisplaying operations in an endpoint or a channel is sometimes not enough. \\nYou can now configure your documentations to show operation verbs in navigation.\\n\\nTo enable it, go to your documentation settings \\"Customize UI\\" tab, then select \\"Groups and operations with verbs\\" in the \\"Navigation\\" input."},{"id":"/2020/11/12/add-a-favicon-to-your-documentation","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2020/11/12/add-a-favicon-to-your-documentation","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2020-11-12-add-a-favicon-to-your-documentation.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2020-11-12-add-a-favicon-to-your-documentation.md","title":"Add a favicon to your documentation","description":"Until now, for documentation having a customised logo, the same one was used as a favicon.","date":"2020-11-12T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"November 12, 2020","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Add a favicon to your documentation","tags":["Improvement"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Show verbs in navigation","permalink":"/product-updates/2020/11/18/show-verbs-in-navigation"},"nextItem":{"title":"Better change summaries","permalink":"/product-updates/2020/07/02/better-change-summaries"}},"content":"Until now, for documentation having a customised logo, the same one was used as a favicon.\\n\\nFrom now on, you can use a specific one, to brighten up your documentation more than ever!\\n\\nHere is how [Bump\'s documentation](https://developers.bump.sh/) looks like now:\\n\\n![Bump doc with favicon.png](/files/changelog/favicon.png)\\n\\nAnd icing on the cake: it works for your [hub](https://docs.bump.sh/help/hubs/) too!\\n\\nHappy enhancement!"},{"id":"/2020/07/02/better-change-summaries","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2020/07/02/better-change-summaries","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2020-07-02-better-change-summaries.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2020-07-02-better-change-summaries.md","title":"Better change summaries","description":"We have enhanced the way we summarize API changes. We now list any changes, at all levels (endpoints, requests, responses, attributes & headers) in the API changelogs and notifications we send.","date":"2020-07-02T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"July 2, 2020","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Better change summaries","tags":["Improvement"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Add a favicon to your documentation","permalink":"/product-updates/2020/11/12/add-a-favicon-to-your-documentation"},"nextItem":{"title":"Documentation examples for lazy people","permalink":"/product-updates/2020/06/12/enhanced-examples"}},"content":"We have enhanced the way we summarize API changes. We now list any changes, at all levels (endpoints, requests, responses, attributes & headers) in the API changelogs and notifications we send.\\n\\nHere an example of a previous summary:\\n\\n```\\nEndpoint updated: Versions\\nEndpoint updated: Validations\\n```\\n\\nWhich now becomes:\\n\\n```\\nUpdated: POST /docs/{:id}/versions\\n  Body attribute added: specification\\n  Response added: 200\\n  Responses removed: 201, default\\nUpdated: POST /docs/{:id}/validations\\n  Body attribute added: specification\\n  Response removed: default\\n```\\n\\nIt is now active for all new deployments. We\u2019ll be recalculating the summaries of previous deployments to make your API changelogs clearer soon."},{"id":"/2020/06/12/enhanced-examples","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2020/06/12/enhanced-examples","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2020-06-12-enhanced-examples.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2020-06-12-enhanced-examples.md","title":"Documentation examples for lazy people","description":"What\'s the first thing you look at when exploring a new tool? If you\'re as lazy as I am, it\'s probably the examples. As we think they are one of the most important parts of your documentation, we gave them the attention they deserve.","date":"2020-06-12T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"June 12, 2020","tags":[{"label":"Improvement","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/improvement"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Documentation examples for lazy people","tags":["Improvement"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Better change summaries","permalink":"/product-updates/2020/07/02/better-change-summaries"},"nextItem":{"title":"Your whole ecosystem on a single page","permalink":"/product-updates/2020/04/24/introducing-hubs"}},"content":"What\'s the first thing you look at when exploring a new tool? If you\'re as lazy as I am, it\'s probably the examples. As we think they are one of the most important parts of your documentation, we gave them the attention they deserve.\\n\\nFirst, we have improved the way we auto-generate examples when missing. We now generate them based on the format of the attribute, for the following formats: email, url, date, date-time and UUID.\\n\\n![Capture d\u2019e\u0301cran 2020-05-22 a\u0300 17.38.56.png](https://cloud.headwayapp.co/changelogs_images/images/big/000/047/932-74090dff60fa2591c44bb291882921e52a6a136c.png)\\n\\nFor requests with a body, we now display the whole body example, just under the cURL command example.\\n\\nAnd last but not least, copying an example has never been easier: we have added a copy button for cURL and request body examples:\\n\\n![May-22-2020 17-45-20.gif](https://cloud.headwayapp.co/changelogs_images/images/big/000/047/934-5691743f4132ecdc68c12f439ffc69a5ccf2729e.gif)"},{"id":"/2020/04/24/introducing-hubs","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2020/04/24/introducing-hubs","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2020-04-24-introducing-hubs.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2020-04-24-introducing-hubs.md","title":"Your whole ecosystem on a single page","description":"Today, we are super excited to release a long-awaited feature: Hubs. You can now create your APIs catalogs, directly from Bump.","date":"2020-04-24T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"April 24, 2020","tags":[{"label":"New feature","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/new-feature"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Your whole ecosystem on a single page","tags":["New feature"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Documentation examples for lazy people","permalink":"/product-updates/2020/06/12/enhanced-examples"},"nextItem":{"title":"Introducing our GitHub action","permalink":"/product-updates/2020/02/20/introducing-our-github-action"}},"content":"Today, we are super excited to release a long-awaited feature: Hubs. You can now create your APIs catalogs, directly from Bump.\\n\\n![home-hub.png](https://cloud.headwayapp.co/changelogs_images/images/big/000/046/230-4d740fb504ecd138814ef507bb3fc4b256fd2118.png)\\n\\nHighlighted features:\\n* custom domain support\\n* documentations can be grouped by tag\\n* default settings at the hub level, applied to all its documentations\\n* auto-creation of hub documentations from your CI\\n* and obviously, OpenAPI and AsyncAPI support\\n\\nHubs are available with our Business plan.  Learn more [on our help center](https://help.bump.sh/hubs)."},{"id":"/2020/02/20/introducing-our-github-action","metadata":{"permalink":"/product-updates/2020/02/20/introducing-our-github-action","editUrl":"https://github.com/bump-sh/docs/tree/main/docs/product-updates/2020-02-20-introducing-our-github-action.md","source":"@site/docs/product-updates/2020-02-20-introducing-our-github-action.md","title":"Introducing our GitHub action","description":"Deploying your API documentation has never been so simple if you are using GitHub. We have just released our GitHub action, which lets you super easily control when and how you want to deploy your doc.","date":"2020-02-20T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"February 20, 2020","tags":[{"label":"New feature","permalink":"/product-updates/tags/new-feature"}],"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[],"frontMatter":{"title":"Introducing our GitHub action","tags":["New feature"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Your whole ecosystem on a single page","permalink":"/product-updates/2020/04/24/introducing-hubs"}},"content":"Deploying your API documentation has never been so simple if you are using GitHub. We have just released [our GitHub action](https://github.com/marketplace/actions/api-documentation-on-bump), which lets you super easily control when and how you want to deploy your doc.\\n\\nAll you have to do is configuring your workflow:\\n\\n```\\nsteps:\\n  - name: Checkout\\n    uses: actions/checkout@v2\\n  - name: Deploy API documentation\\n    uses: bump-sh/github-action@0.1\\n    with:\\n      id: <BUMP_DOC_ID>\\n      token: <BUMP_DOC_TOKEN>\\n      file: doc/api-documentation.yml\\n```\\n\\nYou can see it in action on our [workflow examples](https://github.com/bump-sh/bump-ci-example/tree/master/.github/workflows) \ud83d\ude0e"}]}')}}]);